  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For another part, to expand dataset, annotators meticulously brainstorm application cases where agents are likely to trigger certain risk types in certain scenarios.",
    "Then, with the assistance of ChatGPT and our validity check, application cases are polished into valid ones.",
    "At last, injecAgent (Zhan et al., 2024) contributed 414 samples to the data of Intended Attacks.",
    "81 samples from ToolEmu (Ruan et al., 2024), 24 samples from AgentMonitor (Naihin et al., 2023), along with 55 samples of manual construction from human annotators, constitute the 155 data of Unintended Risks.",
    "R-Judge comprises 569 complex cases where intricate risks lie in the multi-turn interaction between the user, agent, and environment."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
